We considered a specific method defined by Sobol for calculating sensitivity indices65. It provides the relative contribution of the model parameters to the total model variance, here at different times of the simulation. The method relies on the same principle as the analysis of variance. It was designed to decompose the variance of a model output according to the various degrees of interaction between the n uncertain parameters \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${({x}_{i})}_{i\in \{1,n\}}$$\end{document}(xi)i∈{1,n}. Formally, by assuming that the parameter uncertainties are independent, the model output, denoted y, could be expressed as a sum of functions that take parameter interactions into account,20\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$y={f}_{0}+\mathop{\sum }\limits_{i=1}^{n}{f}_{i}({x}_{i})+\mathop{\sum }\limits_{{i,j=1}\atop {i\ne j}}^{n}{f}_{i,j}({x}_{i},{x}_{j})+...+{f}_{1, \, ..., \, n}({x}_{1},...,{x}_{n}).$$\end{document}y=f0+∑i=1nfi(xi)+∑i,j=1i≠jnfi,j(xi,xj)+...+f1,...,n(x1,...,xn).Under independence assumptions between models parameters variability, model variance is:21\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\mathbb{V}}ar}(y)= \, \mathop{\sum }\limits_{i=1}^{n}{{\mathbb{V}}ar}({f}_{i}({x}_{i}))\\ +\mathop{\sum }\limits_{{i,j=1}\atop {i\ne j}}^{n}{{\mathbb{V}}ar}({f}_{i,j}({x}_{i},{x}_{j}))\\ +...+{{\mathbb{V}}ar}({f}_{1, \, ..., \, n}({x}_{1},...,{x}_{n})).$$\end{document}Var(y)=∑i=1nVar(fi(xi))+∑i,j=1i≠jnVar(fi,j(xi,xj))+...+Var(f1,...,n(x1,...,xn)).This variance decomposition leads to the definition of several sensitivity indices. The first-order Sobol’s index of each parameter is,22\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
